.TH CWE-191 7 "2026-06-15" "CWE Top 25 (2025)" "Software Weakness Reference"
.SH NAME
CWE\-191 \- Integer Underflow (Wrap or Wraparound)
.SH RANK
KEV\-referenced weakness. Not part of the 2025 CWE Top 25; documented here because it appears in the CISA KEV catalog.
.SH CLASSIFICATION
Class: KEV\-referenced weakness.
.SH DESCRIPTION
The product subtracts one value from another, such that the result is less than the minimum allowable integer value, which produces a value that is not equal to the correct result. This can happen in signed and unsigned cases.
.SH KNOWN EXPLOITED VULNERABILITIES
CISA KEV catalog (as of 2026-06-15): \fB2\fR exploited CVEs mapped to this weakness.
.PP
CVE\-2014\-0497, CVE\-2021\-31956.
.SH EXAMPLES
One vulnerable\->fixed pair per ecosystem (C).
.SS C
\fIVulnerable:\fR
.RS
.EX
size_t n = recv_len - header_len;   /* underflows if recv_len < header_len */
memcpy(dst, src, n);                /* huge copy */
.EE
.RE
\fIFixed:\fR
.RS
.EX
if (recv_len < header_len) return -1;
size_t n = recv_len - header_len;
memcpy(dst, src, n);
.EE
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBcwe\fR(7) (index).
.PP
